{"tid":2328935,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"【反觀外國】南非憲法法院大多數裁定，公民有權倡議反對惡法，不算煽惑","createTime":"2020-12-17T01:30:24.000Z","updateTime":"2020-12-17T03:33:04.000Z","uid":138409,"like":22,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":11,"replies":[{"pid":"abd2d8fd0c4e88848b2eb2f463223a53b5d90d03","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:30:24.000Z","msg":"然後連登仔繼續恥笑南非係落後國家<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n而家邊個落後啲啊？<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\nbtw<br />\n留意言論自由喺南非嘅context<br />\n係preclude咗hate speech<br />\n<br />\n<blockquote>(2) The right in subsection (1) does not extend to&mdash;<br />\n<br />\n(a) propaganda for war;<br />\n<br />\n(b) incitement of imminent violence; or<br />\n<br />\n(c) advocacy of hatred that is based on race, ethnicity, gender or religion, and that constitute incitement to cause harm.&rdquo;</blockquote><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/EdInDisguise/posts/3566868166759775\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FEdInDisguise%2Fposts%2F3566868166759775&d=c%2B6PkbrQ5MzYtHY5m9tE15X8N1KgQotyuydbLhb69C0%3D&h=5c48fbeb\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/EdInDisguise/posts/3566868166759775</a><br />\n<br />\n有趣，南非極左泛非政黨Economic Freedom Fighters主席2014年公開呼籲黨員佔領屬於其他人的（空置）土地，被控煽惑其他人侵佔土地。<br />\n<br />\n南非憲法法院上個月以7:3大多數裁定，<span class=\"gold\">只要符合民主精神，公民有權反對其認為不義的法律或罪行，亦有權鼓勵 - 只要沒有強迫 - 其他人按其良心違抗惡法。</span>（和香港/英國普通法理解一致、基本上適用於所有實質罪行的）煽惑罪不必要地將並不算嚴重的罪行視為犯罪；即使被告罪成後可能獲得輕判，<span class=\"gold\">但單是暴露於經歷刑事檢控的風險，已足以構成不合比例地違反言論自由。</span><br />\n因此，煽惑罪從此必須以較不侵犯言論自由的方式詮釋：只有煽惑其他人干犯嚴重罪行，方屬犯罪。（法院認為現階段不宜由法庭詳細定義何謂「嚴重罪行」，所以命令國會在24個月內修改法例，但<span class=\"gold\">強調並非只有微不足道（de minimis）的罪行才不算「嚴重」。</span>）<br />\n<br />\n'[51] ... [T]here should be no debate about the need for or benefits of the inchoate crime of incitement.  Its usefulness is mundane.  But, what is inescapable is that legislation that limits free expression <span class=\"gold\">may not do so by proscribing the incitement of just &ldquo;any offence&rdquo;.</span>  The limitation must not extend to minor offences or offences that threaten no serious harm or danger either to individuals, society or public order, property or the economy.  <span class=\"gold\">And by minor, as opposed to serious, offences I have in mind</span> those that may not necessarily fall in the category of the de minimis rule or be covered by the defence of necessity, but <span class=\"gold\">all offences that cannot correctly be described as &ldquo;serious&rdquo; offences.</span><br />\n'[52] Citizens ought to enjoy the liberty to express themselves in support of or opposition to anything or any law, obviously within the confines of the overall thrust of section 16(1) of the Constitution.  <span class=\"gold\">Speaking out or advocacy against laws or offences believed to be unjust ought not to be easily proscribed by statute. And so is encouraging, not forcing, others to defy them.</span>  Allowing that expression would then <span class=\"gold\">leave it open to individuals to make up their own minds &ndash; to follow or reject the incitement &ndash; in line with their constitutional right to freedom of &ldquo;thought&rdquo; and &ldquo;opinion&rdquo;.</span>  The exercise of that freedom would then inform their own response to what they are being incited to say or do.<br />\n[53] ... [M]ost of the citizens of South Africa are not only laypersons, but they are also woefully under-resourced.  They often have no money for basic necessities, talk less of fees for a legal representative to raise defences known to lawyers, when charged for only trying to exercise their fundamental rights.  And even if represented, <span class=\"gold\">grave injustices do happen and justice is sometimes only done after a long and economically, reputationally and emotionally taxing or ruinous judicial process.  Why not avoid this?</span> ...'<br />\n<br />\n- Economic Freedom Fighters v Minister of Justice and Correctional Services [2020] ZACC 25 per Mogoeng CJ<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.saflii.org/za/cases/ZACC/2020/25.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.saflii.org%2Fza%2Fcases%2FZACC%2F2020%2F25.html&d=c%2B6PkbrQ5MzYtHY5m9tE15X8N1KgQotyuydbLhb69C0%3D&h=df2402f1\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">http://www.saflii.org/za/cases/ZACC/2020/25.html</a>"},{"pid":"2f881ff453b774548a996b161e92979bca3216e3","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:30:41.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"e45cb9b285d4098b83c4bea63d605670114fd2b3","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:31:21.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"ef3c46999d5d62d42dd2078568db2a74d57212aa","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:31:45.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"3600bf86e0e05cc7061874cc98e2ed41a4e3bf9c","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:32:36.000Z","msg":"push<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"cbd554c73d92f2b18abd1cfba41adf1bfbca1c79","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:35:11.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"9b4b7f99bd3b1914aa32f0ee8ffb0a614b6672ca","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:36:16.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"8ba38573d80dc106a1cfe710ba3439cf6cc230cb","tid":2328935,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:36:49.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"196a69be2315f4ea4a4daa5add35682c33fdadfd","tid":2328935,"uid":31974,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T01:36:57.000Z","msg":"希望佢地真係得到自己想要既民主<br />\n當年份freedom charter寫完出黎<br />\n同